# Project Rules and Conventions

## Project Overview

This is the `giskard-checks` library - lightweight primitives to define and run checks against model interactions.

## Key Files

- Monorepo root `Makefile` — development workflow (run `make help` from repository root)
- `pyproject.toml` — build configuration, dependencies, and tooling
- `README.md` — end-user documentation and quickstart

## Development Workflow

Always use Makefile commands for development tasks. See [03-development.mdc](03-development.mdc) for the complete workflow.

## Code Quality

- Python >= 3.12 required
- Use Pydantic v2 models for type safety
- Async-friendly: checks can be sync or async
- Follow the existing patterns in the codebase
- Use absolute imports within the `giskard.checks` package

## Testing

- From the repository root: `make test-unit PACKAGE=giskard-checks` for unit tests (or `make test` for all tests including functional)
- Tests are in `tests/` mirroring the package structure
- Static checks aligned with CI: `make check` (after `make install install-tools` if needed)
